metadata.name: Light Years Away #241
metadata.description:
The individual, sitting alone in an abandoned castle, reflects on their past and experiences a sense of collapse and confusion. The once grand halls are now overrun with moss and ancient porcelain scattered throughout the corners, seemingly mocking their current state of mind. However, a ray of light shines through as the clouds part, signaling hope for the future. Through collapse and confusion, the individual strives for peace and freedom, standing with renewed determination and a new perspective.

‧looking back on the past
‧collapse and confusio
‧the clouds part to reveal the light
‧see the future
‧peace and freedom

Controls:
- Press [S] to save the image

Everything is generated with code.
Made with p5.js

Thank you for checking out my art, hope you have a great day.
by xtzfusion.tez

metadata.name: Boundless Realm of Possibilities #68
metadata.description:
Mesmerizing landscapes, towering mountains to rolling hills, verdant forests to winding rivers, this world is teeming with life and adventure. Keep a watchful eye as you journey across this realm, as you may encounter sea dragons lurking in the depths of the oceans. This map may lead you to the greatest treasure.

's' to save
'a' to see the building animation.
'r' to go back to the full image.

metadata.name: Circumscript #85
metadata.description:
It has always been a goal of mine to incorporate the worlds of physical and digital art together in a piece. And with circumscript I am the closest I've ever been. Circumscript uses a custom shader written to mix and "dilute" the colors on the canvas, thus creating a very physical feeling piece.

This dilution can be more or less depending on the edition, but always plays a huge role in the feel of the piece.


Happy new year.


----


[m] or [double tap] : opens the export/settings menu, use this menu to change the resolution, and make sure to press the reload button if you do.
[holding down] : zooms in on a certain area of the piece, depending on where your mouse/finger is. Use this feature to expore the complex textures of the piece in more detail, it's highly recommended to do this on a higher resolution setting.

The outputs can vary slighty per device, as there's a slight difference in how certain math gets interpreted on different devices with shaders.


----


Made with p5.js and webgl by Wouter Missler in 2022/3.
